create an asible role that will perform thee following: 

main.ymlk will include 2 roles pgadmin4.yml and WSO2_DB_CLEANUP.yml
i want to help to create the second ansible playbook WSO2_DB_CLEANUP 
simply gona create crontab -e with the following : 
0 1 * * * /bin/sh /home/cloud-user/WSO2_DB_CLEANUP/CRONS/cron_token_cleanup_runner.sh
0 1 * * * /bin/sh /home/cloud-user/WSO2_DB_CLEANUP/CRONS/cron_session_data_cleanup_runner.sh
0 4 * * * /bin/sh /home/cloud-user/WSO2_DB_CLEANUP/CRONS/cron-stop-process-session-data-cleanup-ruuner.sh
0 4 * * * /bin/sh /home/cloud-user/WSO2_DB_CLEANUP/CRONS/cron-stop-process-token-cleanup-runner.sh

after that will transfer a folder that i will stored on the files of ansible directory 
the folders contain all the crontab and script script and also a directory of logs where the logs data will be stored. the tree of the folders's follow: 
